Open source demo version

Required Instruments for compilation on ubuntu
    gcc, make, cmake 
Depends on followinng libraries 
    png
    opengl   
    freeglut
    freetype
    box2d
    sfml
    lua
    glm
    rapidxml

First Compilation manual for ubuntu users
1) download rapidxml headers from http://sourceforge.net/projects/rapidxml/files/latest/download
    and install it to /usr/include/rapid
2) install dependencies
    sudo apt-get install  \
        libpng++-dev \
        freeglut3-dev \
        libxmu-dev \
        libxi-dev \
        libsfml-dev \ 
        libbox2d-dev \
        libfreetype6-dev \ 
        liblua5.2-dev \
        libglm-dev 
3) git clone https://github.com/lazarev-pv/robot-game.git
4) cd robot-game; mkdir Build; cd Build
5) cmake ../
6) make
Result (all executables need to be launched with working directory Game-Data)
Build/Robot-Character/ched - skeleton animation editor
Build/Robot-Editor/editor - level editor
Build/Robot-Game/robot - game ('a' 'd' to move, space for jumping, 'e' to interact and 's' to strike)








